### req.params

Route parameters parsed into an object:

```javascript
app.get('/users/:id', (req, res) => {
  console.log(req.params.id);
});
```

### req.query

Parsed query string parameters:

```javascript
app.get('/search', (req, res) => {
  // GET /search?q=express&page=2
  console.log(req.query.q);    // 'express'
  console.log(req.query.page); // '2'
});
```

### req.body

Parsed request body (requires body-parsing middleware):

```javascript
app.use(express.json());

app.post('/users', (req, res) => {
  console.log(req.body.name);
});
```

### req.headers

Access request headers as an object:

```javascript
app.get('/', (req, res) => {
  console.log(req.headers['content-type']);
  console.log(req.headers['authorization']);
});
```

### Additional Properties

- `req.ip` â€” Client IP address
- `req.path` â€” The request path
- `req.cookies` â€” Parsed cookies (requires cookie-parser)
- `req.hostname` â€” Hostname from the Host header

codeExample:
app.get('/profile/:username', (req, res) => {
  const { username } = req.params;
  const { tab, page } = req.query;
  const userAgent = req.headers['user-agent'];
  res.json({ username, tab, page, userAgent, ip: req.ip });
});
